e to the population and diversity of languages and culture within China, this has often been the case even with spoken languages. %0a%0aIn 2018, after seven years of research, the China's State Language Commission has finally released an official list of 5,000 common Chinese words in standard CSL. This development will undoubtedly work wonders for bridging divides between speakers of various CSL dialects, bringing awareness to those with hearing disabilities, and helping us all feel more connected.%0a%0aSources: %0ahttps://news.cgtn.com/news/2019-09-23/IDSL-China-s-sign-language-history-dates-back-to-Tang-Dynasty-period-KamfGp0Q1y/index.html%0ahttps://www.whatsonweibo.com/chinese-sign-language-online/%0a%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a(:GradedBy: TA_mason:)
