,000 common Chinese words in standard CSL. This development will undoubtedly work wonders for bridging divides between speakers of various CSL dialects, bringing awareness to those with hearing disabilities, and helping us all feel more connected.%0a%3c %0a%3c Sources: %0a%3c https://news.cgtn.com/news/2019-09-23/IDSL-China-s-sign-language-history-dates-back-to-Tang-Dynasty-period-KamfGp0Q1y/index.html%0a%3c https://www.whatsonweibo.com/chinese-sign-language-online/%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
